<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="118">Host unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="118" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="118">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Eulonchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eulonchus sapphirinus" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapphirinus">Eulonchus sapphirinus</taxonomicName>
is the sister species to the eastern 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Eulonchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eulonchus marialiciae" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marialiciae">Eulonchus marialiciae</taxonomicName>
as both have characteristic bright green metallic colouration, short proboscis, yellow legs and similar shaped male genitalia. The shape of the antennal flagellum and colour of calypter separate the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
